how old do cats live to be?

According to Wikipedia and OpenLibrary, cats typically live between 14 - 18 years in the wild or up to 20 years in captivity. In contrast, domesticated cats tend to have an average lifespan of around 16 years in the US, but can reach even longer lives if healthy and well-cared for.
